Bluetongue, United Kingdom
--------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 27 Sep 2007 from Dr Debby
Reynolds, Director General & Chief Veterinary Officer, Department for
Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (DEFRA), Director General for
Animal Health & Welfare, London, United Kingdom
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 22 Sep 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 23 Sep 2007
Report date: 27 Sep 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 27 Sep 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: bluetongue virus, serotype 8
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: entire country
